1 (5) (i) “Private place” means a room in which a person can reasonably
2 be expected to fully or partially disrobe and has a reasonable expectation of privacy,
3 INCLUDING in:
4 1. an office, business, or store;
5 2. a recreational facility;
6 3. a restaurant or tavern;
7 4. a hotel, motel, or other lodging facility;
8 5. a theater or sports arena;
9 6. a school or other educational institution;
10 7. a bank or other financial institution;
11 8. any part of a family child care home used for the care and
12 custody of a child; [or]
13 9. A RESIDENCE; OR
14 10. another place of PRIVATE OR public use or
15 accommodation.
16 (ii) “Private place” includes a tanning room, dressing room, bedroom,
17 or restroom.
18 (6) (i) “Visual surveillance” means the deliberate, surreptitious
19 observation of an individual by any means.
20 (ii) “Visual surveillance” includes surveillance by:
21 1. direct sight;
22 2. the use of mirrors; or
23 3. the use of cameras.
24 (iii) “Visual surveillance” does not include a casual, momentary, or
25 unintentional observation of an individual.
26 (b) This section does not apply to a person who without prurient intent:
27 (1) conducts filming by or for the print or broadcast media;

